  "origin": {
    "question": "Problem 7.3. Consider the familiar metric space$$\\mathrm {d s}^{2} = \\mathrm {d r}^{2} + \\mathrm {r}^{2} \\mathrm {d} \\theta^{2}.$$(a) Write the 2 equations that result from the geodesic equation, and show that the following are first integrals of these equations:$$r^{2} \\frac {d \\theta}{d s} = R_{0} = c o n s t a n t$$$$\\left(\\frac {\\mathrm {d} \\mathbf {r}}{\\mathrm {d} s}\\right)^{2} + \\mathrm {r}^{2} \\left(\\frac {\\mathrm {d} \\theta}{\\mathrm {d} s}\\right)^{2} = 1.$$",
    "answer": "$$r^2 \\frac{d\\theta}{ds} = R_0 = \\text{constant}$$$$(\\frac{dr}{ds})^2 + r^2 (\\frac{d\\theta}{ds})^2 = 1$$",
